7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Continue and Pieces share a solid foundation of core features including Code Generation, Debugging, Multi Language, Ide Integration. Where Continue pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Autocomplete and Refactoring, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Continue holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Pieces scores 6/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Continue and Pieces offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Continue's free tier and Pieces's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
